 milliseconds at end point (sertraline: 12\%; placebo: 13\%), or other cardiac measures. All comparisons were statistically nonsignificant (P{$>$} or = .05). The incidence of severe cardiovascular adverse events was 14.5\% with sertraline and 22.4\% with placebo. In the total randomized sample, the CGI-I (P =.049), but not the HAM-D (P =.14), favored sertraline. The CGI-I responder rates for sertraline were significantly higher than for placebo in the total sample (67\% vs 53\%; P =.01), in the group with at least 1 prior episode â€¦},
